<h1 class="nhsuk-heading-xl">The case</h1>

<p class="nhsuk-lead-paragraph">
  Sickle cell disease is the UK’s fastest-growing genetic condition. During an acute painful
  crisis, timely analgesia is essential — yet patients frequently wait too long, have to
  re-narrate complex histories while in severe pain, and encounter bias and dismissal.
</p>

<h2 class="nhsuk-heading-l">What the evidence shows</h2>
<p class="nhsuk-body">
  In 2022–23 the {{ site.owner }}, with University Hospitals Bristol and Weston, ran a discovery
  project on acute painful sickle cell care. It found that personalised digital care plans show
  real promise for improving access to, experience of, and accountability of care — but that they
  have not been widely tested or adopted.
</p>

<h2 class="nhsuk-heading-l">What a good care plan can do</h2>

<h3 class="nhsuk-heading-m">Patient safety &amp; clinical care</h3>
<ul class="nhsuk-list nhsuk-list--bullet">
  <li>Faster, personalised analgesia during a crisis — no need to re-narrate history in severe pain.</li>
  <li>Fewer medication and treatment errors; documented opioid tolerance and adverse reactions.</li>
  <li>A clinical record that is harder to override through bias or assumption.</li>
  <li>Plans accessible to 111 / 999 so pre-hospital response is informed; pregnancy flags linking obstetrics and haematology.</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="nhsuk-heading-m">Care continuity &amp; coordination</h3>
<ul class="nhsuk-list nhsuk-list--bullet">
  <li>A persistent, portable plan that travels with the patient — including to non-specialist or unfamiliar hospitals.</li>
  <li>Smoother transition from paediatric to adult services; fewer duplicate diagnostics.</li>
  <li>Flags for unmet referral needs (pain, psychology, social care, obstetrics) and prompts for timely review.</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="nhsuk-heading-m">Accountability</h3>
<ul class="nhsuk-list nhsuk-list--bullet">
  <li>A co-produced, portable record patients can use to challenge inconsistent or substandard care.</li>
  <li>A log of who was involved in each episode, and patterns of delay or dismissal — supporting targeted improvement.</li>
  <li>Post-encounter feedback that generates patient-reported experience data for commissioners and providers.</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="nhsuk-heading-m">Policy, practice &amp; research</h3>
<ul class="nhsuk-list nhsuk-list--bullet">
  <li>Better needs assessment and capacity planning from real-world crisis data.</li>
  <li>Feeds into registries, dashboards and research datasets (with consent) to reduce variation and inform commissioning.</li>
</ul>

